Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.86,0:00:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}The dreams embraced by a single life{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.86,0:00:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}are boundless beyond even the stars.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.87,0:00:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}The dreams that we foster over time{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.88,0:00:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}are waiting for the moment{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}when we come upon them.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.55,0:00:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}The words we exchange{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}make our hearts tremble,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.56,0:00:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}and a chance meeting{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}could change the future.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.23,0:01:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}People, no matter who they are,{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}as they pursue their dreams,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.51,0:01:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}have the courage to travel new paths.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.18,0:01:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}As we leave behind a living{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}testament of our journey,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.52,0:01:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}the Galaxy Railways on which{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}we travel continue ever on.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.88,0:01:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Train stations...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.68,0:01:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}they are a place where greetings{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}and farewells take place over and over.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.55,0:01:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}People wave, and say to each other,{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}"see you later."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.89,0:01:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}However, everyone knows that{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}there are farewells in life{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.29,0:01:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}where you will never{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}see the other person again.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.23,0:02:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Even so, they still say, "see you later."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.51,0:02:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}"Harsh Verdict"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.27,0:02:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Just a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.28,0:02:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is the one that you liked.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Drink as much as you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.56,0:03:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Don't cry. He hated moping, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.24,0:03:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}In tribute to Bruce J. Speed,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}all hands, salute!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.21,0:04:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Was this fate, too?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.90,0:04:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Bruce, the man who shot you\N{\c&He1e1e1&}has been arrested.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.25,0:04:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The SDF is not a death squadron!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.15,0:04:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If you mean to commit suicide,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}go somewhere else!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.92,0:04:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I don't need a gun\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to help people in this job.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.59,0:04:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If you think you can get by with\N{\c&He1e1e1&}that utopian attitude of yours,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.06,0:04:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}then leave the SDF right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.93,0:04:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If you wish to stay, then carry this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.27,0:04:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Is that an order?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.94,0:04:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.60,0:05:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Understood. I will carry it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.88,0:05:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You're too soft, rookie.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.55,0:05:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If that hadn't been broken,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}you'd have kicked the bucket just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.22,0:05:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Are you trying to get both you\N{\c&He1e1e1&}and that criminal killed!?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.52,0:05:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The SDF is not a death squadron!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.22,0:05:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You're the one who told me that, Bruce!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.56,0:05:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Shoot the Grim Reaper! Bruce!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.23,0:05:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Stop that!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.57,0:05:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.90,0:05:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}you have to give it up now, right?\N{\c&He1e1e1&}The name "Bruce the Grim Reaper"?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.25,0:05:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Thanks, Manabu.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.26,0:05:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Bruce, you dumb bastard! Why did you have\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to die!? Why, in a place like that!?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.93,0:05:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}you dumb bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.87,0:06:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If only I hadn't gotten hurt,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Bruce wouldn't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.20,0:06:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I should have been the one to die!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.21,0:06:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Please don't blame yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.84,0:06:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If you say that, then I believe {\i1}Bruce-san{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&}would lament it more than anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.22,0:06:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}David, is it okay\N{\c&He1e1e1&}if I keep this harmonica?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.22,0:06:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Ask him. you were Bruce's star pupil.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.56,0:06:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Bruce, please let me keep this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.24,0:06:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.58,0:06:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Bruce...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.58,0:06:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}W- what do you know!? What does a rookie\N{\c&He1e1e1&}like you know about the SDF!? Eh!? Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.92,0:06:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Stop it, Bruce!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.59,0:07:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.53,0:07:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm sorry. I went a little too far.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.53,0:07:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Look, just keep it within bounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.20,0:07:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain, Sirius Platoon here\N{\c&He1e1e1&}is like a family to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.20,0:07:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}When I saw how he wants\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to do everything as he pleases,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.27,0:07:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}yet he can't do anything for himself,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I couldn't help myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.87,0:07:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Family, huh? So, what you're trying\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to say is that I'm your old man?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.21,0:07:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Whoa, please don't start with\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the "old man" gags, Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.88,0:07:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.22,0:07:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm sorry. I've inadvertently\N{\c&He1e1e1&}given myself away.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.89,0:07:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}you bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.90,0:07:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Bulge, you've been summoned to appear
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.80,0:07:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}before an official\N{\c&He1e1e1&}regulatory board of inquiry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.24,0:07:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.24,0:07:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Board of inquiry? What for?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.91,0:07:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Why the captain?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.24,0:07:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It's that Ivanov bastard.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Now he's done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.58,0:07:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.92,0:07:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.92,0:08:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What's this all about, Captain Murase?\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.52,0:08:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Easy, Yuuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.86,0:08:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.86,0:08:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is part of my duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.53,0:08:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.53,0:08:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain Bulge's actions at this time
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.04,0:08:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}are in clear violation of article 23,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}paragraph 5 of the official regulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.71,0:08:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Consequently,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.54,0:08:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}in my judgment, he should\N{\c&He1e1e1&}be given a harsh sentence.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.54,0:08:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Schwanheld {\i1}Bulge-kun{\i0}, do you\N{\c&He1e1e1&}have any opposing arguments?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.21,0:08:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I do not. I would just point out\N{\c&He1e1e1&}that the matters
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.15,0:08:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}pertaining to the existence of\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the Alfort Cluster Imperial Forces...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.55,0:08:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}...and the {\i1}Cosmo Matrix{\i0} that I reported
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.69,0:08:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}have been expunged\N{\c&He1e1e1&}from Director Ivanov's record.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.89,0:08:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Special Intelligence has\N{\c&He1e1e1&}taken charge of those matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.23,0:08:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}They have nothing\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to do with this inquiry!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.57,0:08:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}However, if we delay our response,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}there will be no going back...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.24,0:08:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Silence! There is no way I am going\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to allow that information to get out!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.91,0:09:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The matter of the Alfort Cluster\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Imperial Forces is under investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.85,0:09:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}You do not need to worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.52,0:09:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Violation of official regulations,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}as well as assaulting a superior officer,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.49,0:09:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}are both serious offenses.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.19,0:09:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Bulge-kun,{\i0} until the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}board reaches its decision,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.26,0:09:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}you are relieved of duty\N{\c&He1e1e1&}as platoon captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.53,0:09:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Sirius Platoon is also\N{\c&He1e1e1&}hereby temporarily disbanded.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.86,0:09:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.20,0:09:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Everything has been\N{\c&He1e1e1&}taken out of your hands now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.54,0:09:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yo.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.21,0:09:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Special Intelligence is working on it,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.58,0:09:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}but they apparently aren't buying\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the alternate dimension thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.55,0:09:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}They're not paying any\N{\c&He1e1e1&}attention to the {\i1}Cosmo Matrix{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.88,0:09:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.89,0:09:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What are you going to do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.22,0:09:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'll do whatever I need to.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.22,0:09:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That sounds like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.56,0:09:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}But why? Please answer me, Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.23,0:09:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain, you were just trying\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to protect {\i1}Big One,{\i0} weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.90,0:09:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is outrageous!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.90,0:10:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The fact is, I did disregard orders,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}assault a superior officer,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.08,0:10:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and allow Bruce to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.24,0:10:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's not what I'm saying!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.25,0:10:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Are you just going to step down like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.48,0:10:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Are you going to take the blame\N{\c&He1e1e1&}for everything, and resign!?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.25,0:10:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I have no intention of\N{\c&He1e1e1&}voluntarily resigning.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.82,0:10:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}But I do intend to accept\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Headquarters' decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.59,0:10:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}How can you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.26,0:10:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Manabu!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.26,0:10:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What would you tell Bruce!?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.60,0:10:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey! Stop, Manabu!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.27,0:10:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.94,0:10:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki, you're in Vega Platoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.94,0:10:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Louis, you're in Spica Platoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.61,0:10:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}David, you've been assigned\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to Rigel Platoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.28,0:10:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuki, you'll be on ground duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.94,0:10:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}No way! I'm not going\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to follow that order!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.61,0:10:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}If you don't like it, then quit.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}The personnel listed will report
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.52,0:10:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}to each of their platoons\N{\c&He1e1e1&}starting tomorrow. That is all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.29,0:10:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Please have faith in the captain.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm sure he has something in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.24,0:11:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's it. Make sure\N{\c&He1e1e1&}that part is nice and tight.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.57,0:11:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}who is the maintenance chief here?\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Respond!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.24,0:11:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}So, he's here, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.25,0:11:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That would be me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.25,0:11:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I am Ivanov, from Special Intelligence.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Get over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.59,0:11:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What can I do for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.92,0:11:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}There should have been a small item\N{\c&He1e1e1&}that {\i1}Big One{\i0} was analyzing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.26,0:11:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Are you the one who removed it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.59,0:11:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Let's see, did I find\N{\c&He1e1e1&}anything like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.26,0:11:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hand it over.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.26,0:11:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Gee, where did I put it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.26,0:11:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Don't screw with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.60,0:11:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Oh, come to mention it...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.27,0:11:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Do you mean this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.94,0:11:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Special Intelligence\N{\c&He1e1e1&}will take charge of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.94,0:11:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Thank you for all of your efforts.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.28,0:11:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}to hell with this thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.91,0:12:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We're almost to Planet Hyde.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.91,0:12:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}All right. Commence deceleration.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.91,0:12:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.92,0:12:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki! You're not here as a guest!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.92,0:12:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Stop spacing off.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.59,0:12:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Bruce!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.93,0:12:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Snap out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.27,0:12:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.28,0:12:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.22,0:13:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Bruce...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.89,0:13:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.89,0:13:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.24,0:13:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.58,0:13:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}you stupid bastard!\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Are you trying to get killed!?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.25,0:13:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.58,0:13:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yuuki, I know how you feel about Bruce.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}But focus on the task at hand now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.59,0:13:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.59,0:13:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I know it hurts right now...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.59,0:13:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain Murase, what will\N{\c&He1e1e1&}happen to Captain Bulge?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.60,0:13:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Galaxy Railways Headquarters\N{\c&He1e1e1&}isn't made up of fools.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.63,0:13:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Have some faith in\N{\c&He1e1e1&}what we've been defending.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.94,0:13:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is hardest on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.89,0:14:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Bruce...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.56,0:14:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I cannot see the fate\N{\c&He1e1e1&}of the Galaxy Railways.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.23,0:14:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It is only hidden. It is\N{\c&He1e1e1&}certain to come into view again.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.57,0:14:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Where exactly are the Alfort Cluster\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Imperial Forces coming from?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.57,0:14:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That is still unknown.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.91,0:14:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Forgive the intrusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.24,0:14:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I realize I am overstepping my authority,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.04,0:14:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}but I need to speak with you,\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Supreme Commander Layla Destiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.58,0:14:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.58,0:14:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.25,0:14:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Special Intelligence has already submitted\N{\c&He1e1e1&}its report to the Supreme Commander.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.92,0:14:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This is no place for\N{\c&He1e1e1&}someone like you to be!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.26,0:14:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Get lost!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.26,0:14:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Sorry to bother you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.55,0:15:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.22,0:15:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Buddy, you got my clothes wet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.23,0:15:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.90,0:15:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Okay, that's the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.24,0:15:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What's the matter? It's your turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.93,0:15:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Bruce-san...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.55,0:16:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Don't act so cocky, buddy!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.89,0:16:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It means that we will be fighting\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to protect the entire universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.89,0:16:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The entire universe...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.56,0:16:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Including these guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.23,0:16:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Bruce, I don't understand anymore...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.90,0:16:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Just what is it that we've been\N{\c&He1e1e1&}protecting up to now? Answer me, Bruce.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.91,0:16:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Yuuki-kun...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.58,0:16:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Louis...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.54,0:17:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Receiving a message\N{\c&He1e1e1&}from the advance force.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.91,0:17:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Some of them have encountered\N{\c&He1e1e1&}elements of resistance,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.55,0:17:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}but they were successful in penetrating\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the galaxy in the other dimension.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.89,0:17:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}General Foresis,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.55,0:17:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}the setup of the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}dimension opener is complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.56,0:17:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Activate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.23,0:17:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.57,0:17:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The energy is stable.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.57,0:17:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}No enemies detected on the other end.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.24,0:17:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}How much time will it take for\N{\c&He1e1e1&}the dimension hole to be opened?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.91,0:17:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I anticipate it will take 20 weeves.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.25,0:18:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That's too slow.\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Have it done in 10 weeves.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.52,0:18:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}But, that could be\N{\c&He1e1e1&}hazardous to the systems!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.53,0:18:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That is an order.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.87,0:18:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The captain's coat...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.54,0:18:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I believe in the captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.88,0:18:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I believe in him, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.22,0:18:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Well, see you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.23,0:18:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Good morning. I brought you some snacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.57,0:18:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hey, I owe you one.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.24,0:18:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Nah, don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.91,0:19:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Well, we're in your debt\N{\c&He1e1e1&}for all you did for Old Man Whitman.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.11,0:19:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}This makes us even.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.85,0:19:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}By the way, how is\N{\c&He1e1e1&}that other thing coming?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.85,0:19:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}That is going to be a little\N{\c&He1e1e1&}difficult. Give us a little more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.52,0:19:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Things are becoming urgent.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.52,0:19:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Is the situation really that dangerous?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.86,0:19:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.53,0:19:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}The board has reached its decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.86,0:19:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Schwanheld {\i1}Bulge-kun{\i0}, you are to be\N{\c&He1e1e1&}relieved of your command of Sirius {\i1}Platoon,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.87,0:19:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}and stripped of your eligibility\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to be a member of the force.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.88,0:19:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What a waste...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.55,0:19:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Hold on! What's going on!?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.88,0:19:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Is it true!? The captain was dismissed!?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.55,0:19:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.22,0:19:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.56,0:19:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We received word from\N{\c&He1e1e1&}Captain Bulge a little while ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.89,0:19:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}He said that everyone should\N{\c&He1e1e1&}do what they ought to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.90,0:19:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What we ought to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.90,0:19:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Division mobilization orders!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.57,0:19:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}All platoons, please follow\N{\c&He1e1e1&}your instructions and mobilize!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.57,0:20:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}We've confirmed the location\N{\c&He1e1e1&}of the unidentified battleship
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.34,0:20:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}that disappeared in Coulomb space!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.57,0:20:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}It has appeared somewhere above the\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Harloom{\i0} track! Maximum alert level!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.24,0:20:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Dispatch all platoons\N{\c&He1e1e1&}to the scene at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.58,0:20:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What are you going to do, Manabu?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.25,0:20:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}I'm going.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.58,0:20:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Louis, be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.59,0:20:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Louis-san, isn't that nice?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.26,0:20:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}What? Is there something going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.93,0:20:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}David, you be careful, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.27,0:20:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Bruce, I'm going to{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}do what I need to now.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.27,0:20:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Magnetic barrier\N{\c&He1e1e1&}generator systems normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.27,0:20:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Energy normal. Pressure within the\N{\c&He1e1e1&}boiler is rising. Cylinder valves open.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.28,0:20:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Engage main circuits.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.61,0:20:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Engaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.28,0:20:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Systems all green!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.28,0:20:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Iron Berger,{\i0} move out!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.57,0:21:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}Once again, young people leave\N{\c&He1e1e1&}from the main terminal planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.94,0:21:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&}to take back the fate that\N{\c&He1e1e1&}is no longer visible to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.24,0:21:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}What lies on the other{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}side of our farewells?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.58,0:21:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Once the pain of parting is overcome,{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}people find the light of hope.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.27,0:21:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}How many nights have{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}I spent alone since then?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.28,0:22:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Constantly having dreams of the hope{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}that you are, as I lightly sleep.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.96,0:22:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}The smiles and tears that{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}you gave to me and me alone{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.98,0:22:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}come to mind every time{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}I get disheartened,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.32,0:22:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}and I set forth again toward the morrow.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.99,0:22:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}The joyful light of{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}the galaxy beckons me{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.66,0:22:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}to that beloved person within my heart.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.67,0:22:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}No matter how far apart we are,{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}my memories will never fade.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.34,0:23:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}My heart wishes always{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}to be at your side.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.70,0:23:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}The Alfort forces possess{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}an overwhelming power.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.37,0:23:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}The lifelines of the universe{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}are being torn apart.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.04,0:23:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}What is it you're after?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.37,0:23:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Next time on Tales of the Galaxy Railways,{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}Episode 24:{\i0} "The Galaxy Ablaze"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.71,0:23:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}We're going to encounter{\i0}\N{\c&He1e1e1&\i1}something at the next station.{\i0}